The paper discusses security threats in wireless sensor networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). It also mentions the use of wireless communication technology, which is a subfield of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also talks about the need for addressing security concerns from the beginning of system design, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the interaction of sensor networks with sensitive data, which is related to system and control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the processing power of sensor nodes, which is related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
